{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3505572,"name":"Magnus Nelson","username":"Magnus-Nelson","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/c77e96/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-02-07T23:29:59.544Z","cooked":"

Hi everyone,

I’m running into an issue where our robot code won’t deploy due to an error in the PathPlanner autobuilder. When attempting to deploy, I get the following error:

Unhandled exception instantiating robot com.pathplanner.lib.commands.PathPlannerAuto
java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke “Object.toString()” because the return value of “org.json.simple.JSONObject.get(Object)” is null
Error at com.pathplanner.lib.commands.PathPlannerAuto.(PathPlannerAuto.java:96): Unhandled exception instantiating robot com.pathplanner.lib.commands.PathPlannerAuto
java.lang.NullPointerException: Cannot invoke “Object.toString()” because the return value of “org.json.simple.JSONObject.get(Object)” is null
at com.pathplanner.lib.commands.PathPlannerAuto.(PathPlannerAuto.java:96)
at com.pathplanner.lib.commands.PathPlannerAuto.(PathPlannerAuto.java:63)
at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.AutoBuilder.buildAutoChooserWithOptionsModifier(AutoBuilder.java:432)
The robot program quit unexpectedly. This is usually due to a code error.
The above stacktrace can help determine where the error occurred.
See https//wpilib.org/stacktrace for more information.
at com.pathplanner.lib.auto.AutoBuilder.buildAutoChooser(AutoBuilder.java:391)
at frc.robot.RobotContainer.(RobotContainer.java:90)
Could not instantiate robot com.pathplanner.lib.commands.PathPlannerAuto!
at frc.robot.Robot.(Robot.java:17)
at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:370)
at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.startRobot(RobotBase.java:510)
at frc.robot.Main.main(Main.java:13)
Error at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:383): The robot program quit unexpectedly. This is usually due to a code error.
The above stacktrace can help determine where the error occurred.
See https//wpilib.org/stacktrace for more information.
Error at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:389): Could not instantiate robot com.pathplanner.lib.commands.PathPlannerAuto!

From what I can tell, the error originates in the PathPlannerAuto constructor, where a call to JSONObject.get(Object) is returning null and then trying to call .toString() on that null value. This results in a NullPointerException and prevents the robot from instantiating properly.

I’m not entirely sure if this is due to a misconfiguration in our JSON auto files, a version incompatibility between PathPlanner and WPILib, or an issue within the library itself. Has anyone encountered a similar problem or found a workaround for this? Any suggestions on debugging or resolving this issue would be greatly appreciated.

Thanks in advance for any help!

Contribute to 2147chuck/2025-CHUCK-Code development by creating an account on GitHub.

—
[Additional context: I’ve checked our JSON files for any obvious issues, and everything seems to be in order on our end. Any insights into what key might be missing or how to better handle this null value would be helpful.]
